From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2009 08:29:20 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 053/365] posix-timers: Prevent broadcast signals
Origin: https://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/rt/linux-stable-rt.git/commit?id=0575e3afe41576f4ede6b9e531fb6b8baeb7cb18

Posix timers should not send broadcast signals and kernel only
signals. Prevent it.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
---
 kernel/time/posix-timers.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/kernel/time/posix-timers.c b/kernel/time/posix-timers.c
index 0e6ed2e7d066..06ef7e413209 100644
--- a/kernel/time/posix-timers.c
+++ b/kernel/time/posix-timers.c
@@ -526,6 +526,9 @@ static struct pid *good_sigevent(sigevent_t * event)
 	case SIGEV_THREAD:
 		if (event->sigev_signo <= 0 || event->sigev_signo > SIGRTMAX)
 			return NULL;
+		if (sig_kernel_only(event->sigev_signo) ||
+		    sig_kernel_coredump(event->sigev_signo))
+			return NULL;
 		/* FALLTHRU */
 	case SIGEV_NONE:
 		return task_pid(rtn);
